LAGOS – Members of Ikeja Exclusive Lions Club under the headship of Lion Irene Chukwudumebi Ikpeazu, has again attracted commendations and applauses for their giant stride in touching the lives of the common people in the society. The club’s hands of fellowship to the residents of Akora Village in Adeniyi Jones area of Lagos through its core project, general upgrade and donation of medical equipment to the Primary Health Centre in Akora Village got it the latest accolades. Lion Ikpeazu said during the commissioning of the project on Wednesday, “I made it public during my investiture that my legacy project would be on health, and I am glad that it has come to pass. I am delighted, with support of my members, that we are able to deliver on our promise. To the glory of God, we painted the entire building and equipped the facility with mattresses, pillows, bed sheets, fridge, patients’ seats, air conditioning units, fans, window blinds, thermometers, spymaster and drip stands.”